  "uncertainty_notes": "Ranking research institutions is inherently subjective and fluctuates annually. This ranking balances raw publication volume at top-tier venues (CVPR, ICCV, ECCV)—where institutions like Tsinghua and NTU excel—with paradigm-shifting historical impact (citations), where corporate labs like Google, Meta, and Microsoft, alongside Stanford and Berkeley, dominate. Furthermore, corporate labs frequently co-author papers with academic institutions, making the exact attribution of 'influence' complex. The exact ordering between closely matched institutions is debatable and depends on whether one weights recent publication volume or historical, foundational breakthroughs more heavily."
